					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2156983&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225333" alt="psul" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2156983)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;" >psul</a></span> <span class="odate time_1447060857 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Nov 2015 09:20</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2404561">
									

<p>This is an expansion of the story started in <a href="/scp-2162">SCP-2162</a>. It's about looking at the same thing in different ways, and what that can reveal.</p>
<p><strong>Attributions:</strong> As I said in the skip comments, very many thanks to:</p>
<ul>
<li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1379080&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1447060857" alt="Randomini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1379080)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;">Randomini</a></span> for letting me use Agent Green. My headcanon is that this is set a little before <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/the-cool-war-hub">The Cool War</a>.</li>
<li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1735681&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1447060857" alt="TwistedGears" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1735681)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;">TwistedGears</a></span> for letting me use Agent Navarro. I hadn't read all of the Navarro-starring work before writing this, so it probably skews closest to the Navarro of <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/learning-the-alphabet-hub">Learning the Alphabet</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p>When I was thinking about an agent for this investigation, I asked for permission from both TG and Randomini, as I knew both Green and Navarro had a connection to anart. I never imagined that I would get permission from both of them, and the more I thought about it, the more I liked the idea of the two characters working together.</p>
<p>&quot;Michael Cavendish&quot; is with permission from and great thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rioghail" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1302192); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1302192&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1447060857" alt="Rioghail" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1302192)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rioghail" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1302192); return false;">Rioghail</a></span>, whose <a href="/scp-2071">SCP-2071</a> includes the original character (from the early 1800s) and provided mine with an alias.</p>
<p><strong>Acknowledgements:</strong> Thanks also to everyone who reviewed this on the forums and chat. Decibelles, WrongJohnSilver, Dr Hood, Dr Solo and sirpudding.</p>

							</div>

								
					
