					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2156983&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225333" alt="psul" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2156983)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;" >psul</a></span> <span class="odate time_1447092722 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Nov 2015 18:12</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2404783">
									

<p>Clearly it is made up of supplementary materials, and I don't think it makes sense without having read the SCP first, which suggests that it is a Supplement.</p>
<p>However its purpose is to tell a story, and I also think it needs the bookend as a bit of an additional hook (and restatement of the theme), so Tale also seems appropriate.</p>
<p>In the end, it falls somewhere in between, so I am happy to be guided by consensus on how to label it. Could it have both labels, or is that taboo?</p>

							</div>

								
					
