					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1324229"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1447168515 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Nov 2015 15:15</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2405290">
									

<p>This does expand the story and helps to explain some of the <em>why</em>, but the <em>why</em> isn't particularly interesting.</p>
<p>There's nothing particularly distinctive about this narrative. &quot;Eager beaver young person gets involved in anomalous stuff, gets in over their head<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-779492-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-779492-1')">1</a></sup>&quot; isn't really a new story on the wiki. I didn't really feel anything for Baker at the end other than a vague &quot;huh, that's unfortunate.&quot; Basically, this feels like a largely uninteresting expansion to an already-uninteresting story.</p>
<p>I will say that I liked the actual procedural stuff, though. It's nice to see the Foundation find stuff out with handwaving it (&quot;something something hacking communications something something surveillance&quot;). Still, I gotta go with a downvote.</p>
