<p>Fair enough. Thanks for reading on after the SCP, thanks very much for sharing your thoughts, and I'm glad that you liked the procedural at least.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I didn't really feel anything for Baker at the end other than a vague &quot;huh, that's unfortunate.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That is a shame. Part of the formal challenge I set myself here was to make Robert Baker a character (and ideally a somewhat sympathetic, somewhat nuanced character) without him ever appearing in the story - to be blatantly expository, the idea was to have his story as the ground and the procedural be the figure. Clearly character is something I can work on for my next submission.</p>

